==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wiljan'', from Indo-European ''*wel-''.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[willian]] (Dutch [[willen]]), Old Norse [[vilja]] (Swedish [[vilja]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌹𐌻𐌾𐌰𐌽]]; the alternative form ''*waljan'' gave Old High German [[wollen]] (German [[wollen]]).  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[velle]], Slavic ''*velěti'' (Old Church Slavonic [[велѣти]], Russian [[велеть]]), Baltic ''*wel-'' (Lithuanian [[velmi|vélmi]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈwɪl:an/}}

===Verb===
'''willan''' (irregular)
# to [[wish]], to [[want]]

